results.name: Number of Ramanujan primes R_k such that 2^(n-1) < R_k <= 2^n.
link: Dana Jacobsen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..56
program: (PARI) \\ With RR[.] is a list of A104272(.). The output of this program is (for n>=1) n, A190502(n), and RR[a(n)], a(n).
(Perl) use ntheory ":all"; say "$_ ",ramanujan_prime_count(1 << $_) - ramanujan_prime_count(1 << ($_-1)) for 0..56; # _Dana Jacobsen_, May 05 2017
